Willas-Array Electronics (Holdings) Limited Key Developments

Willas-Array Electronics (Holdings) Limited Approves Final Dividend for the Financial Year Ended March 31, 2017
Jul 28 17
Annual general meeting of the Willas-Array Electronics (Holdings) Limited held on July 28, 2017 approved a final dividend of HKD 0.31 per share for the financial year ended March 31, 2017.


Willas-Array Electronics (Holdings) Limited Proposes Final Dividend for the Year Ended March 31, 2017, Payable on August 25, 2017
Jun 26 17
Willas-Array Electronics (Holdings) Limited proposed to declare a final dividend of HKD 0.31 per ordinary share for the financial year ended March 31, 2017, for approval at the AGM to be held on July 28, 2017. Subject to the receipt of Shareholders' approval at the AGM, the final dividend will be paid on August 25, 2017.


Willas-Array Electronics (Holdings) Limited, Annual General Meeting, Jul 28, 2017
Jun 26 17
Willas-Array Electronics (Holdings) Limited, Annual General Meeting, Jul 28, 2017, at 09:30 Singapore Standard Time. Location: Mandarin Orchard Singapore, Grange Ballroom Level 5, Main Tower, 333 Orchard Road Singapore Singapore Agenda: To read, consider and adopt the Directors' report and audited financial statements of the company for the financial year ended March 31, 2017 together with the Independent Auditors' report thereon; to declare a final dividend of HKD 0.31 per ordinary share for the financial year ended March 31, 2017; to approve the proposed Directors' fees for the financial year ending March 31, 2018; to re-elect Mr. Leung Chun Wah as an executive Director of the company; to re-elect Mr. Kwok Chan Cheung as an executive Director of the company; to re-appoint Messrs. Deloitte Touche Tohmatsu, Hong Kong as the independent Auditors of the company and to authorise the Directors to fix their remuneration; to consider authority to allot and issue new ordinary shares in the share capital of the company; and to consider authority to purchase or acquire shares in the share capital of the company under the share buyback mandate; and to consider other matters.


